Ralph Chapoteau (born 1954) is a Haitian painter. Born in Gonaves, Chapoteau attended the Fine Arts Academy beginning in 1974. His work was first exhibited in 1978 and has since been displayed throughout the Caribbean, including Santo Domingo and Guadeloupe. 
